The Malloy Data Model

Step 1: Understanding the Iowa Liquor Market Using Malloy

Liquor sales in Iowa are state-controlled, with all liquor wholesale run by the state. All purchases and sales of liquor that stores make are a matter of public record. We are going to explore this data set to better understand the Iowa Liquor market.

All data here is stored in BigQuery, in the table 'bigquery-public-data.iowa_liquor_sales.sales'.

The Malloy data model can be reviewed in examples under 'iowa'.

A quick overview of the dataset:

  • Date/Time information (`date`)

  • Store and Location (store_name, store_address, store_location, city, county, and zip_code)

  • Vendor information (vendor_name, vendor_number)

  • Item information (item_number, item_description, category, category_name)

  • Volume Information (bottle_volume_ml, bottles_sold, volume_sold_liters, volume_sold_gallons)

  • Pricing information (state_bottle_cost, state_bottle_retail, and sale_dollars)

Using a Malloy Query to Examine the Contents of the Table

The table below shows all columns in the data set and their most common or ranges of values. The Malloy query below (or a derivation of it) can be used to examine just about any dataset.

    "other_columns": [
      {
        "column_name": "bottle_volume_ml",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 378000"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "bottles_sold",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 15000"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "date",
        "ranges_of_values": "2012-01-03 to 2022-03-31"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "pack",
        "ranges_of_values": "1 to 336"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "sale_dollars",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 279557.28"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "state_bottle_cost",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 7680"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "state_bottle_retail",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 11520"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "volume_sold_gallons",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 3962.58"
      },
      {
        "column_name": "volume_sold_liters",
        "ranges_of_values": "0 to 15000"
      }
    ]
  }
]
WITH __stage0 AS (
  SELECT
    group_set,
    CASE group_set
      WHEN 0 THEN 'invoice_and_item_number'
      WHEN 1 THEN 'date'
      WHEN 2 THEN 'store_number'
      WHEN 3 THEN 'store_name'
      WHEN 4 THEN 'address'
      WHEN 5 THEN 'city'
      WHEN 6 THEN 'zip_code'
      WHEN 7 THEN 'store_location'
      WHEN 8 THEN 'county_number'
      WHEN 9 THEN 'county'
      WHEN 10 THEN 'category'
      WHEN 11 THEN 'category_name'
      WHEN 12 THEN 'vendor_number'
      WHEN 13 THEN 'vendor_name'
      WHEN 14 THEN 'item_number'
      WHEN 15 THEN 'item_description'
      WHEN 16 THEN 'pack'
      WHEN 17 THEN 'bottle_volume_ml'
      WHEN 18 THEN 'state_bottle_cost'
      WHEN 19 THEN 'state_bottle_retail'
      WHEN 20 THEN 'bottles_sold'
      WHEN 21 THEN 'sale_dollars'
      WHEN 22 THEN 'volume_sold_liters'
      WHEN 23 THEN 'volume_sold_gallons'
    END as fieldName,  CASE group_set
      WHEN 0 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 1 THEN 'date'
      WHEN 2 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 3 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 4 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 5 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 6 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 7 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 8 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 9 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 10 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 11 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 12 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 13 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 14 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 15 THEN 'string'
      WHEN 16 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 17 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 18 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 19 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 20 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 21 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 22 THEN 'number'
      WHEN 23 THEN 'number'
    END as fieldType,  CASE group_set
      WHEN 0 THEN base.invoice_and_item_number
      WHEN 2 THEN base.store_number
      WHEN 3 THEN base.store_name
      WHEN 4 THEN base.address
      WHEN 5 THEN base.city
      WHEN 6 THEN base.zip_code
      WHEN 7 THEN base.store_location
      WHEN 8 THEN base.county_number
      WHEN 9 THEN base.county
      WHEN 10 THEN base.category
      WHEN 11 THEN base.category_name
      WHEN 12 THEN base.vendor_number
      WHEN 13 THEN base.vendor_name
      WHEN 14 THEN base.item_number
      WHEN 15 THEN base.item_description
    END as fieldValue,
   COUNT(*) as weight,
    CASE group_set
      WHEN 99999 THEN ''    WHEN 1 THEN MIN(CAST(DATE(base.date) AS STRING )) || ' to ' || MAX(CAST(DATE(base.date) AS STRING ))
      WHEN 16 THEN CAST(MIN(base.pack) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.pack) AS STRING)
      WHEN 17 THEN CAST(MIN(base.bottle_volume_ml) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.bottle_volume_ml) AS STRING)
      WHEN 18 THEN CAST(MIN(base.state_bottle_cost) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.state_bottle_cost) AS STRING)
      WHEN 19 THEN CAST(MIN(base.state_bottle_retail) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.state_bottle_retail) AS STRING)
      WHEN 20 THEN CAST(MIN(base.bottles_sold) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.bottles_sold) AS STRING)
      WHEN 21 THEN CAST(MIN(base.sale_dollars) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.sale_dollars) AS STRING)
      WHEN 22 THEN CAST(MIN(base.volume_sold_liters) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.volume_sold_liters) AS STRING)
      WHEN 23 THEN CAST(MIN(base.volume_sold_gallons) AS STRING) || ' to ' || CAST(MAX(base.volume_sold_gallons) AS STRING)
    END as fieldRange
  FROM `bigquery-public-data.iowa_liquor_sales.sales` as base
  CROSS JOIN (SELECT row_number() OVER() -1  group_set FROM UNNEST(GENERATE_ARRAY(0,24,1)))
  GROUP BY 1,2,3,4
)
, __stage1 AS (
  SELECT
    fieldName,
    fieldType,
    COALESCE(fieldValue, fieldRange) as fieldValue,
    weight
  FROM __stage0
)
, __stage2 AS (
  SELECT
    group_set,
    CASE WHEN group_set IN (1,2) THEN
      base.fieldName
      END as column_name__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN
      count(distinct base.fieldValue)
      END as cardinality__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      base.fieldValue
      END as fieldValue__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN
      SUM(base.weight)
      END as rows_matched__2,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      base.fieldName
      END as column_name__3,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      base.fieldValue
      END as ranges_of_values__3
  FROM `__stage1` as base
  CROSS JOIN (SELECT row_number() OVER() -1  group_set FROM UNNEST(GENERATE_ARRAY(0,3,1)))
  WHERE ((group_set NOT IN (1,2) OR (group_set IN (1,2) AND base.fieldType='string')))
  AND ((group_set NOT IN (3) OR (group_set IN (3) AND IFNULL(NOT(base.fieldType='string'),FALSE))))
  GROUP BY 1,2,4,6,7
)
, __stage3 AS (
  SELECT 
    CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN 1  ELSE group_set END as group_set,
    CASE WHEN group_set IN (1,2) THEN
      column_name__1
      END as column_name__1,
    ANY_VALUE(CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN cardinality__1 END) as cardinality__1,
    ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=2 THEN STRUCT(
      fieldValue__2 as fieldValue, 
      rows_matched__2 as rows_matched
      ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  rows_matched__2 desc  LIMIT 20) as values_list_detail__1,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      column_name__3
      END as column_name__3,
    CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN
      ranges_of_values__3
      END as ranges_of_values__3
  FROM __stage2
  GROUP BY 1,2,5,6
)
SELECT
  ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=1 THEN STRUCT(
    column_name__1 as column_name, 
    cardinality__1 as cardinality, 
    values_list_detail__1 as values_list_detail
    ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  cardinality__1 asc ) as string_columns,
  ARRAY_AGG(CASE WHEN group_set=3 THEN STRUCT(
    column_name__3 as column_name, 
    ranges_of_values__3 as ranges_of_values
    ) END IGNORE NULLS  ORDER BY  column_name__3 asc ) as other_columns
FROM __stage3

   base.invoice_and_item_number as invoice_and_item_number,
   base.date as date,
   base.store_number as store_number,
   base.store_name as store_name,
   base.address as address,
   base.city as city,
   base.zip_code as zip_code,
   base.store_location as store_location,
   base.county_number as county_number,
   base.county as county,
   base.category as category,
   base.category_name as category_name,
   base.vendor_number as vendor_number,
   base.vendor_name as vendor_name,
   base.item_number as item_number,
   base.item_description as item_description,
   base.pack as pack,
   base.bottle_volume_ml as bottle_volume_ml,
   base.state_bottle_cost as state_bottle_cost,
   base.state_bottle_retail as state_bottle_retail,
   base.bottles_sold as bottles_sold,
   base.sale_dollars as sale_dollars,
   base.volume_sold_liters as volume_sold_liters,
   base.volume_sold_gallons as volume_sold_gallons
FROM `bigquery-public-data.iowa_liquor_sales.sales` as base
LIMIT 100
